Business Brief -- Fibronics International Inc.:
   Deficit Totaling $2.2 Million
   Is Posted for Fourth Period
The maker of fiber optic data communications devices said
it introduced a significant number of complex, new products
last year that consumed greater than expected human resources
and expense.
   After taking into account its product introduction
difficulties, Fibronics said it wrote down the value of its
inventory by $1.5 million to $15.8 million.
   In 1991, Fibronics had a loss of $3.3 million, or 52 cents
a share, on revenue of $54 million. In 1990, it had net
income of $3.8 million, or 59 cents a share, after a $910,000
extraordinary credit for tax-loss carry-forwards. Revenue was
$63 million.